<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05013j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05013j">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05013j"> 13(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> spirits of beasts &darr; men &uarr;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The true meaning of &ldquo;the breath of life&rdquo; is indicated in the Revised Version, both in Genesis and Ecclesiastes (iii.), where the writer sneers at those who speak of the breath or <mark>spirit of the man as going upward to heaven at death, and the breath or spirit of the beast as going downward to the earth</mark>. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [The Creation Story] 23</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
